        {
          "ability": {
            "ability_type": "offensive",
            "name": "Consecrated",
            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "As long as the consecrate ritual effects persist in Crownhold, a Gorumite warpriest gains a +1 status bonus to attack rolls, skill checks, saving throws, and Perception checks; these bonuses are not calculated into the stat block.",
            "type": "stat_block_section"
          },
          "name": "Consecrated",
          "offensive_action_type": "ability",
          "subtype": "offensive_action",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        {
          "ability": {
            "ability_type": "offensive",
            "action_type": {
              "name": "Reaction",
              "subtype": "action_type",
              "type": "stat_block_section"
            },
            "effect": "The Gorumite warpriest loudly proclaims the glory of Gorum. The next divine spell they cast takes one fewer action (minimum of one), but must only target the warpriest. If the spell affects an area or multiple targets, such as bless, it only affects the warpriest, even if it lasts more than one round.",
            "frequency": "once per day",
            "name": "Fervent Casting",
            "subtype": "ability",
            "traits": [
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 16,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Auditory",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 453,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 48,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "243cd4d729d5eddd1e2c4635b7985fb9",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Divine",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 455,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "This magic comes from the divine tradition, drawing power from deities or similar sources. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to divine magic.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 107,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "771980a2b2ed7b7e83f96ac0cf2001b5",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Spellshape",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 302",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 302",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 302,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Actions with the spellshape trait tweak the properties of your spells. You must use a spellshape action directly before casting the spell you want to alter. If you use any action (including free actions and reactions) other than casting a spell directly after, you waste the benefits of the spellshape action. The benefit is also lost if your turn ends before you cast the spell. Any additional effects added by a spellshape action are part of the spell's effect, not of the spellshape action itself.",
                "type": "trait"
              }
            ],
            "type": "stat_block_section"
          },
          "name": "Fervent Casting",
          "offensive_action_type": "ability",
          "subtype": "offensive_action",
